{"body":"You could get GBP 86.45 a week if you care for someone at least 35 hours a week. You need to spend at least 35 hours a week caring for someone. If you live in Scotland, you need to apply for Carer Support Payment instead of Carer's Allowance.","citation_label":"GOV.UK Carer's Allowance eligibility","citation_path":"uk/guidance/govuk/carers-allowance/eligibility","document_class":"guidance","expression_date":"2026-06-06","heading":"Carer's Allowance eligibility","id":"b6e222b5-d903-5ec9-a1e9-96eb4d50631f","jurisdiction":"uk","kind":"guidance","language":"en","legal_identifier":"GOV.UK Carer's Allowance eligibility","level":1,"metadata":{"retrieved_at":"2026-06-06T08:16:38Z"},"ordinal":1,"parent_citation_path":"uk/guidance/govuk/carers-allowance","source_as_of":"2026-06-06","source_document_id":"govuk/carers-allowance/eligibility","source_format":"gov.uk-html","source_id":"https://www.gov.uk/carers-allowance/eligibility","source_path":"sources/uk/guidance/2026-06-06-uk-govuk-carers-allowance-eligibility.html","source_url":"https://www.gov.uk/carers-allowance/eligibility","version":"2026-06-06-uk-govuk-carers-allowance-eligibility"}
